data.chText: 午餐，午宴（正式的午餐或正式用语）
data.enText: a formal lunch or a formal word for lunch

data.chText: 夫人，午餐在一点钟开始。
data.enText: Luncheon will be served at one, Madam.

means: 午餐，午宴(正式的午餐或正式用语)

value.def: A luncheon is a formal lunch, for example to celebrate an important event or to raise money for charity.

example.ex: Earlier this month, a luncheon for former UN staff was held in Vienna.
example.tran: 本月早些时候在维也纳设午宴招待了前联合国工作人员。

value.def: Luncheon is the meal that you eat in the middle of the day. It is usually called lunch.

example.ex: Promptly at one, luncheon was served...
example.tran: 午饭一到一点钟就上桌了。

trans: (英国某些雇主提供的可在餐馆用餐或在商店换取食物的)午餐券
